        h3 Course Objectives
            ol
                li Design and implement programs that require
                ol(type="a")
                    li various control statements involving selection and repetition
                    li expressions with variables, constants, function calls, pointers, and arithmetic/relational operators with mixed data
                    li arrays, strings, and other data structures
                    li library functions and programmer-defined functions with parameter-passing by value and by reference
                    li abstraction, modularity, separation of concerns
                    li use of the object-oriented programming model
                li Debug programming syntax and run-time errors.
                li Produce recursive algorithms, and choose appropriately between iterative and recursive algorithms.
                li Describe and apply basic software engineering design principles and software quality factors.



