        h3 Attendance Policy
        ul.none
            li Class attendance is not required, but it is STRONGLY ENCOURAGED.  There are unannounced in-class exercises factored into your final grade.
            li When a class is missed, it is the STUDENT'S responsibility to obtain any notes, assignments, etc. from classmates.
            li Lab attendance is required. YOU WILL RECEIVE A ZERO FOR ANY UNEXCUSED MISSED LABS. A zero lab grade cannot change!!!
            li Excused absences must be approved by your lecture instructor. BE PROACTIVE!!!
            li Students are still responsible for lab work missed even when their absence was excused.
            li Students can ONLY make-up in-class exercises with an approved absence. BE PROACTIVE!!!
            li Please, be on time for lecture AND turn off your cell phone ringer because it can be disruptive to other students, as well as the instructor.
            li Laptops and other electronics are not allowed during lecture, unless approved by the instructor. There is a study that shows you lower yours and your peer's grade by using a laptop in the classroom: <a style="color:#0000FF" href="http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/laptop-use-lowers-student-grades-experiment-shows-1.1401860">Laptop Study</a>. In addition, there are studies that show traditional note taking by hand aids in a student's learning: <a style="color:#0000FF" href="http://chronicle.com/blogs/linguafranca/2014/08/25/why-im-asking-you-not-to-use-laptops/?cid=cr&amp;utm_source=cr&amp;utm_medium=en">Another Study</a>. Our course requires those who have authorization by the instructor to sit in a particular section of the classroom to prevent distracting others.
            li If the instructor is late for a lecture or a TA is late for lab, please remain in the classroom for 10 minutes.
            li You must remain in the lab until (your work is complete or until the lab period has ended) and viewed/graded by a lab instructor.


